data.current_description: Applies one or more updates to the presentation. Each request is validated before being applied. If any request is not valid, then the entire request will fail and nothing will be applied. Some requests have replies to give you some information about how they are applied. Other requests do not need to return information; these each return an empty reply. The order of replies matches that of the requests. For example, suppose you call batchUpdate with four updates, and only the third one returns information. The response would have two empty replies: the reply to the third request, and another empty reply, in that order. Because other users may be editing the presentation, the presentation might not exactly reflect your changes: your changes may be altered with respect to collaborator changes. If there are no collaborators, the presentation should reflect your changes. In any case, the updates in your request are guaranteed to be applied together atomically.
data.summary_suggestion: Apply multiple updates to a presentation atomically
data.description_suggestion: Applies one or more updates to a presentation in a single atomic transaction. Accepts a BatchUpdatePresentationRequest containing an array of update requests. All requests are validated before application; if any request is invalid, the entire batch fails and no changes are applied. Returns a BatchUpdatePresentationResponse with replies corresponding to each request in ordersome updates return information while others return empty replies. Updates are applied atomically and guaranteed to succeed together, though collaborator edits may alter the final result. Note: In multi-user environments, concurrent edits may modify your changes.
